ext_descriptions.ext_description:
The rule compatible_dimension ensures that 

all geometric_representation_items are geometrically founded in one or more geometric_representation_contexts;

when geometric_representation_items are geometrically founded together in a coordinate space, they have the same coordinate space dimension_count by ensuring that each matches the dimension_count of the coordinate space in which it is geometrically founded.Two-dimensional geometric_representation_items that are geometrically founded in a geometric_representation_context are only geometrically founded in geometric_representation_contexts with a coordinate_space_dimensino of 2.  All geometric_representation_items founded in such a context are two-dimensional.  All other values of dimension_count behave similarly.
